                            MSU = Œ£<sub>m=1</sub><sup>43,382</sup> (s<sub>m</sub>a<sub>m</sub> - d<sub>m</sub>a<sub>m</sub>)<sup>2</sup>
                        </div>
                        <div class="formula-note">
                            <strong>Lower bound:</strong> Each SNP inherited independently<br>
                            <strong>Biological meaning:</strong> Minimum possible Mendelian sampling variance<br>
                            <strong>Reality:</strong> True MS variance lies between MSU and MSC
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

