                                <div class="step-specs">
                                    <strong>Model:</strong> Bayesian (Bayes A) with heavy-tailed priors<br>
                                    <strong>Innovation:</strong> Accounts for few large-effect and many small-effect QTL<br>
                                    <strong>Parameter:</strong> h = 1.12 (controls departure from normality)<br>
                                    <strong>Shrinkage:</strong> Small effects regressed toward zero, large effects preserved
                                </div>
                                <p><strong>Statistical sophistication:</strong> This model captures the biological reality that most SNPs have tiny effects while a few have substantial impact on traits.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="flow-step">
